<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>There is currently no way to specify the unix_socket option for the PDO_MYSQL DSN.
See <a href="http://www.php.net/manual/en/ref.pdo-mysql.connection.php">http://php.net/manual/en/â€¦</a></p>

<p>The desired usage is:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$driver_options = array('unix_socket' =&gt; '/path/to/mysql.sock');
$params = array('driver_options' =&gt; $driver_options, ...other options...);
$db = Zend_Db::factory('pdo_mysql', $params);
</code></pre>

<p>The MySQLI extension doesn't need any change, because the socket location is specified in a php.ini configuration.</p>

